Date: Sat, 30 Aug 1997 10:33:39 -0600
From: Gayle Knapp <gayle@cybersym.com>
[Message abstracted by Moderator]
Not having access to the Lancet report, it's difficult to evaluate the
statistical reliability of the data. But this report raises questions: Do
squirrels get spongiform encephalopathy? Is there a species heirarchy in the
capacity of the protein(s) involved to produce/induce the necessary
conformational change(s)? Does the incidence with which scrapie, BSE, etc.
occur increase with greater cross-species feeding of nervous tissues? i.e.,
does incidence of scrapie increase with feeding of cattle tissue from cattle
that in turn were fed sheep tissues?
